The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Air-India will operate a non-stop flight from Calcutta to London from June 18. The flight on the Delhi-Dhaka-Calcutta-London route will run thrice a week ? on Tuesdays, Thursdays and Saturdays. A Boeing 777-200 aircraft ? with 272 seats (12 first class, 49 executive class and 211 economy class) ? will be operated, an airline spokesperson said.

 Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) will set up a leadership development institute in Salt Lake at a cost of Rs 5 crore. CII chief mentor Tarun Das met chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee at Writers? Buildings on Thursday and briefed him about the project. According to Das, the government has allotted two acres in Sector III for the institute.

 Prabhu Shankar Agarwal, arrested for allegedly plotting to kill a tea stall-owner, was remanded in judicial custody till June 30 by the chief metropolitan magistrate?s court on Thursday. Agarwal, owner of the Haldiram chain of outlets, was arrested at Palam airport, in Delhi, on June 7. Gyanwant Singh, deputy commissioner(I), detective department, said Agarwal had confessed to police that he had engaged extortionist Gopal Tiwari to murder the stall owner.

 A 30-year-old woman was critically injured after being knocked down by an unidentified vehicle in Lover?s Lane, in the Maidan area, on Thursday morning. Police said she was admitted to SSKM Hospital. 

 Gouranga Bhattacharya, alias Bunty, and Bhola Bhatta were arrested in Baguiati on Wednesday night in connection with the murder of promoter Sushil Saha on May 21. Superintendent of North 24-Parganas police Praveen Kumar said the two were picked up from a house in Narayantala. They reportedly told police that they had been engaged by someone to kill the Baguiati-based promoter. 

 Jiten Das, 69, was crushed under the wheels of an unidentified vehicle on Mahatma Gandhi Road on Thursday morning. Police said the mishap occurred while Das was sleeping beside a vat.

 A gold Radha-Krishna idol was recovered from the well in a cloth trader?s house in Baruipur on Thursday. The trader told police that the idol did not belong to his family. The cops suspect that it had been stolen from a temple in Sonarpur. The priest of the temple will be shown the idol.

 Ganesh Thakur, 18, was injured after being hit by a private bus at the crossing of Brabourne Road and India Exchange Place on Thursday morning. He was admitted to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital. The bus was impounded and the driver arrested.

 Sonari Gharai, 25, was arrested in Lake Town on Wednesday night for allegedly hurling bombs on Rajarhat police station officer-in-charge Prabir Roy a few days ago. A pipe-gun and some cartridges were seized from Gharai. 

